                    { "tt0780624", "Rodman Flender", "Some people believe that children are the future and that no child should be left behind. But when the principal of Francis Drake High School hires his smart-aleck slacker friend to take over the gifted and accelerated class, some of the other teachers are worried that the future of these kids does not look very bright at all. Appearances are not everything in this comedy where one teacher's somewhat selfish passion for life makes an amazing impact on a group of students that goes well beyond anyone's expectations. Acclaimed actor Peter Dinklage (The Station Agent) creates a lovable curmudgeon in the tradition of Archie Bunker. It's a rich offbeat comedy that proves inspiration can come from the most unlikely sources, like teenagers.", "N/A", "01 May 2005", "Testing Bob" },
                    { "tt0782157", "Theodore Melfi", "Robert \"Bob\" Bobson has a problem, \"he loves Ikea, he loves everything about it.\" As a boy, young Bobby was infatuated with Ikea furniture and grew up building everything from lamps and chairs to wall units. Anything and everything he could get his hands on. As little Bobby grew up, his passion for the Ikea product grew along with him and eventually led to his position with the company: Director of Marketing, North America. The high profile promotion, coupled with the excitement of the annual Spring Sale, caused Bob to develop a rather peculiar disorder: \"Ikea Specific Tourettes-Like Syndrome.\" The disease advanced quickly, and what started as simple ticks and spouting furniture 'profanities,' soon advanced to complete obsession, sexual dysfunction and indecent exposure. After extensive testing and no cure in site, the Ikea Corporation was compelled to remove Bob from his position and affectively suspend the annual Spring Sale indefinitely. \"The Story Of Bob\" provides for us an inside glance into this troubling new disorder. Through reenactments, and never before seen interviews, the filmmakers were able to explore the inner workings of Ikea Corporation and the troubling Ikea-Obsessed world of Robert Bobson.", "N/A", "12 Dec 2005", "The Story of Bob" },
                    { "tt0787439", "N/A", "(A.C.T.S.)American Collegiate Talent Search with Bob Hope, was the pre- \"Star Search\" and \"American Idol\" talent search program on PBS. It showcased the up and coming student talent found on the college and university campuses of America.", "N/A", "N/A", "The American Collegiate Talent Search with Bob Hope" },
