                    { "tt1338558", "Christopher Blackmon, Brandon Reich", "Two High School guys assist their friend, Bob Zula, In obtaining his much needed closure from his newly ex-girlfriend Jamie. Bob quickly makes the transition from a passive, timid young man, and enters an immediate state of regression from the \"answers\" Jamie gives him. Did I mention that this all takes place in the front yard of Jamie's house?", "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZjRkMGVkY2MtZjU1YS00MzE1LWExYjQtYjM0NGU4YmE2OTg1XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTk4Nzg5NjM@._V1_SX300.jpg", "26 Mar 2009", "The Bob Zula" },
                    { "tt1339077", "Warren Dudley, Roger O'Hara", "Troy Klassen, an American investigative reporter and his film crew follow Private Investigators Dogberry Boyle and Bob Degg, as they solve crime the only way British Private Investigators know how: by humorously botching up their leads creating chaotic comedic capers and belly laughs en route. The comedy receives an added dynamic with the arrival of Jo, Bob's ex flame who is unwittingly drawn into the pair's crime solving escapades and whose straight to the point approach compliments the bumbling comedy duo. Her facial expressions alone deliver as much clout as a successful stand ups signature punch line.", "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMWMyMzQ0ZmMtOGE3My00OWY5LWE4NDQtM2JiMWMxOTc4OTVlXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjg2Njk2MzU@._V1_SX300.jpg", "19 Apr 2008", "Dogberry and Bob: Private Investigators" },
                    { "tt1342446", "N/A", "It's a complete talk show in just five minutes! Monologue joke, desk bit &amp; celebrity interview... who could want more?!", "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMzliNzdiNzAtMzg2Yy00ZmQyLWFhMDgtZGU0ZDhiMjBiNTViXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMzI4OTI2NQ@@._V1_SX300.jpg", "18 Dec 2008", "Anytime with Bob Kushell" },
