                    { "tt1371755", "N/A", "Anyone who has ever heard the Bob and Tom Show on the radio knows that it is impossible to bottle the essence and nuances in the format of a television show. Being able to see the hosts of the show and numerous comedians is nice, but not at all needed to truly get the true spirit of the radio show. It is always hard to summarize how truly great the show is in such a short time frame. The situation is very similar to Jim Rome is Burning. The radio shows are infinitely better than the television shows will ever be. At least Bob and Tom is the live recording of the radio show, Jim Rome's show is simply a regurgitation. The show also leaves a lot to be desired as far as the camera work goes. The only thing it seems to really highlight is how little the hosts seem to actually pay attention to the guests. Funny to watch, but leaves a sense of Bob and Tom not caring and being off in their own worlds.Watchable but not a Must See by any means.", "N/A", "03 Nov 2008", "The Bob & Tom Show" },
