                    { "tt1382183", "Joel Gilbert", "Drummer Winston Watson performed 400 shows with Bob Dylan over five years, traveling the world 10 times over. Watson energized Dylan fans and Bob Dylan himself with his joyful and dynamic ...", "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjAwYjY3NzMtZjMyOS00ODFlLWI1ZTctM2E0ZWZkMjJlM2Y0XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQ0NzE0MQ@@._V1_SX300.jpg", "07 Apr 2009", "Bob Dylan Never Ending Tour Diaries: Drummer Winston Watson's Incredible Journey" },
                    { "tt1392984", "Jim White", "Suffering from a severe stuttering disability, Bob \"Butterbean\" Love, the son of a sharecropper, rose to become a Chicago Bulls NBA superstar, whose records were eventually surpassed by Michael Jordan. After a career ending back injury he was told by doctors that he would have difficulty walking, let alone play the game he loved. His life spiraled out of control and he ended up penniless, working as a busboy and dishwasher at a Seattle restaurant.", "N/A", "N/A", "Find Yourself a Dream: The Bob Love Story" },
                    { "tt1408327", "Patrick E. McCabe", "Bob Swamp has always been a little... different. But when a chance encounter in a restaurant leads to a new relationship, Bob thinks he may have finally found happiness. Unfortunately for Bob, temptation lurks around every corner.", "N/A", "N/A", "Swamp Love: A Bob Swamp Adventure" },
                    { "tt1423343", "David Pring-Mill", "\"Bob vs. Society\" chronicles a few days in the life of a misanthrope named Bob. Bob is a washed-up energy trader who now ekes out a living in New York City by working in a comic book store. Naturally, Bob's marriage with his young wife, Kate, has deteriorated to its final stages. Bob likes to amuse himself by bothering customers, strangers and Kate's friends. He also likes to get his drink on. However, Bob is about to find out what happens when society fights back.", "N/A", "N/A", "Bob vs. Society" },
