                    { "tt1833040", "Thomas Vincent", "This film is based on the true character of Robert Denard (known as Bob Denard) in the 60's when he fights in Democratic Republic of Congo. As a mercenary, he defends President Mobutu who won his position after a putsch. Despite pressures from the French government who supports Mobutu's opponent Moïse Tshombé, Denard stays loyal to Mobutu until the very end when he unsterdands Mobutu wants him dead. Denard's only solution becomes to get rid of Mobutu, however the French governmet ends up changing side to support Mobutu. Luckily for him Denard manages to be rescued after head injury during combat against Mobutu's troops...", "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNDUwNWU0YjItNWE2Zi00YWM5LWI4OGItZGFjZWQ0MGE5MjQ4XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjI2OTc1NDQ@._V1_SX300.jpg", "08 Jun 2018", "Mister Bob" },
                    { "tt1833657", "Will Meugniot, Paul Sabella, Davis Doi", "In their new home of Fixham Harbour, Bob and the team set to work tackling exciting new building jobs and making new friends. But when Spud and Scrambler learn of an amazing treasure - the pirate Brickbeard's Golden Hammer, hidden somewhere in Fixham they decide that building can wait, and they must find the hammer to give to Bob.", "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTQzNjcyMDI3OV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODU1NTA2MDE@._V1_SX300.jpg", "01 Nov 2009", "Bob the Builder: The Legend of the Golden Hammer" },
                    { "tt1885206", "Joel Gilbert", "When Bob Dylan turns 70, his iconic career will have spanned five decades. Yet, a true portrait of the reclusive \"voice of the generation\" has eluded Dylan fans. Through exclusive insider interviews, and never-before-seen photos and footage spanning Dylan's 50-year career, Bob Dylan Revealed offers an intimate biography of who Bob Dylan was, and who he is today. Personal accounts cover Dylan's 1962 Greenwich Village days, his first Electric Tour in 1966, his 1967 stint in drug rehab disguised as a motorcycle accident, his 1974 Comeback Tour, the Desire Album and Rolling Thunder Revue of 1975-1976, his 1978 Entertainer Tour, Dylan's born-again Christian era of 1979-1981, his return to Judaism, and today's ongoing Bob Dylan Never Ending Tour.", "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjI1OTYwOTk4M15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMjY3NTA2MDE@._V1_SX300.jpg", "01 May 2011", "Bob Dylan Revealed" },
                    { "tt1886479", "Jacob Langhoff", "Bob's aging body no longer allows him to completely participate in the Sunday fetish that has sustained him throughout his life. His favorite dominatrix, Belle, reluctantly guides him through his pitiful last attempt at finding the real meaning behind his unusual desires.", "N/A", "N/A", "Bob" },
