                    { "tt4378126", "Jochen Taubert", "If you look at modern day movies most of them just suck. The Story is bad, the script is awful, the set is a blue-screen, just one actor does a decent job and there's millions of dollars worth of special effects. That pretty much summarizes like every big blockbuster of 2014 and most likely 2015.So there is a certain \"aww this will be bad anyway\" mood when I'm watching a movie. This one however deserves something like a couple of anti-Oscars for the acting, the effects, the story, the direction, the producing, the set, the script, the music and everything because I cant possibly imagine anything to be worse than it is. Usually trash movies are at least funny but this one somehow manages to as fun as.... I cant even think of a decent comparison.But after watching this mess I promise you that you will look at all the other movies with a different perspective. You'll start to appreciate the acting of a Kristen Steward, the story of a Transformers movie and even jar-jar binks stepping into poo doesn't look that bad anymore.So in the end this movie is about 70min of pure pain but you get a lot for watching it. Have a try, see how long you can bare to watch it, make bets with your friends if you like.", "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZTVlY2FlMDktNDI1My00M2UzLWI5MDAtMTlmOWU4YTVmZWE4XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMzA5MTg5Mw@@._V1_SX300.jpg", "10 May 2014", "Baggerführer Bob" },
